Description: Lip and wall sherd of East Greek (South Ionian?) pottery small closed vessel; everted rim above baggy shoulder; pale orange clay with much silver mica; band painted at top of shoulder; inscription cut on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 301)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 668, no. 262)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.939)
